The minister of Information and Culture, Alhaji Lai Mohammed, has said that the revival of the Argungu Motor Rally, which usually herald the annual Argungu International Fishing and Cultural Festival, is a testimony to the success of the Muhammadu Buhari administration’s efforts at restoring peace and security in the country, especially in the North East zone. Mohammed stated this when he flagged off the 2020 Argungu Motor Rally at the Eagle Square in Abuja, yesterday. The minister, who represented President Buhari at the event, said the fact that only vehicles assembled in Nigeria are participating in the rally shows the administration’s commitment to building local capacity and diversifying the economy through manufacturing. He said that another attribute of the Argungu Motor Rally is that it will promote tourism in the country.